---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import LogoMark from '../components/LogoMark.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Our Story — Built for the In-Between | STAK Clothing"
  description="The STAK story — built for the in-between. Small runs, real places, made to last. Austin, Texas."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
    { name: 'Story', path: '/story' },
  ]}
>
  <main>
    <section class="page-hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">Story</p>
      <h1 class="display">Built for the <em>in-between.</em></h1>
    </section>

    <section class="story-page-prose">
      <div class="story-page-prose-inner">
        <p class="lede">
          The morning meeting and the desert detour. The city block and the hill country roads. STAK is for the day that keeps shifting on you.
        </p>
        <p>
          We make small runs of essentials in Austin, Texas — built from heavyweight cottons, garment-dyed for character, and finished with details that hold up after the hundredth wash. No seasonal noise. No trend chasing. Just pieces you'll reach for first.
        </p>
        <a href="/journal/what-in-between-means" class="link-underline">Read the field note →</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="story-page-mark">
      <div class="story-page-mark-inner">
        <LogoMark class="grid-mark grid-mark-large" />
        <div class="story-page-mark-text">
          <p class="eyebrow">The Mark</p>
          <h2 class="display">Four letters.<br/>One grid.</h2>
          <p>
            The STAK grid is stamped on every piece — not as decoration, but as a quiet signature. S, T, A, K in four quadrants. A mark you recognize without reading it. Like a camp flag on a ridgeline, or a patch worn soft on a favorite jacket.
          </p>
          <p>
            We make small runs in Austin, Texas. Heavyweight cottons, garment-dyed for depth, finished with details that hold up after the hundredth wash. When a drop is done, it's done. We move on to the next one.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="editorial">
      <div class="editorial-header">
        <p class="eyebrow">Worn here</p>
        <h2 class="display">From one to the other.</h2>
        <p class="editorial-sub">Real days. Real light. No retouching. From Texas to the coast.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="editorial-grid">

        <article class="ed-card ed-card-tall">
          <img src="/austin.jpg" alt="Austin Texas downtown skyline at sunrise" class="ed-card-photo" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
          <div class="ed-card-overlay" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div class="ed-stamp">
            <span class="ed-num">No. 01</span>
            <span class="ed-dot">●</span>
          </div>
          <div class="ed-place-wrap">
            <h3 class="ed-place">Austin</h3>
            <span class="ed-region">Texas, USA</span>
          </div>
          <div class="ed-meta">
            <div><span>30.27° N</span><span>97.74° W</span></div>
            <div class="ed-shot">35mm · Morning</div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="ed-card">
          <img src="/boulder.jpg" alt="Boulder Colorado mountain landscape" class="ed-card-photo" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
          <div class="ed-card-overlay" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div class="ed-stamp">
            <span class="ed-num">No. 02</span>
            <span class="ed-dot">●</span>
          </div>
          <div class="ed-place-wrap">
            <h3 class="ed-place">Boulder</h3>
            <span class="ed-region">Colorado, USA</span>
          </div>
          <div class="ed-meta">
            <div><span>40.01° N</span><span>105.27° W</span></div>
            <div class="ed-shot">35mm · Noon</div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="ed-card">
          <img src="/manhattan-beach.jpg" alt="Manhattan Beach California pier at sunset" class="ed-card-photo" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
          <div class="ed-card-overlay" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div class="ed-stamp">
            <span class="ed-num">No. 03</span>
            <span class="ed-dot">●</span>
          </div>
          <div class="ed-place-wrap">
            <h3 class="ed-place ed-place-long">Manhattan Beach</h3>
            <span class="ed-region">California, USA</span>
          </div>
          <div class="ed-meta">
            <div><span>33.88° N</span><span>118.41° W</span></div>
            <div class="ed-shot">35mm · Golden Hour</div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="ed-card ed-card-tall">
          <img src="/terlingua.jpg" alt="Terlingua Texas desert landscape at dusk" class="ed-card-photo" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
          <div class="ed-card-overlay" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div class="ed-stamp">
            <span class="ed-num">No. 04</span>
            <span class="ed-dot">●</span>
          </div>
          <div class="ed-place-wrap">
            <h3 class="ed-place">Terlingua</h3>
            <span class="ed-region">Texas, USA</span>
          </div>
          <div class="ed-meta">
            <div><span>29.32° N</span><span>103.62° W</span></div>
            <div class="ed-shot">35mm · Dusk</div>
          </div>
        </article>

      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="pillars">
      <div class="pillars-header">
        <p class="eyebrow">The Standard</p>
        <h2 class="display">Three things, done right.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="pillars-grid">
        <div class="pillar">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 60 60" class="pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M5 50 L20 25 L30 35 L42 18 L55 50 Z" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2"/>
            <circle cx="45" cy="15" r="3" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2"/>
          </svg>
          <h3>Limited Runs</h3>
          <p>We make a small run of each piece, then we move on. No restocks, no archive sales. When it's gone, it's part of someone's story.</p>
          <p>A short run means every shirt gets more than inspected. It gets held up. Turned over. Tried on by someone in the room before it goes in the bag.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 60 60" class="pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <circle cx="30" cy="30" r="22" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2"/>
            <path d="M30 8 L30 52 M8 30 L52 30" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2"/>
            <path d="M30 30 L42 18 L36 36 Z" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.6"/>
          </svg>
          <h3>Real Places</h3>
          <p>Every drop is shot in a real place, on a real person, on a real day. No studios, no stylists. The clothes earn the catalog.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 60 60" class="pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <rect x="12" y="12" width="36" height="36" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2"/>
            <path d="M12 30 L48 30 M30 12 L30 48" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.2"/>
            <circle cx="30" cy="30" r="5" fill="currentColor"/>
          </svg>
          <h3>Made to Last</h3>
          <p>Heavyweight cottons, double-needle stitching, garment-dyed for depth. The kind of build that gets better with the years on it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
